WEBVTT


00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:02.920
We crisscrossed France to write this history book

00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:03.683
positive. 

00:00:03.683 --> 00:00:04.360
At reporter,

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:06.240
on they invent 1 ecological world,

00:00:06.600 --> 00:00:07.600
1book that brings together

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:10.080
1 dozen reports to help you discover

00:00:10.360 --> 00:00:11.840
alternatives to the ecological crisis.

00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:13.053
Because yes, 

00:00:13.053 --> 00:00:14.360
other worlds are possible.

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:15.560
We talk about women

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:17.480
who build houses in raw earth,

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:19.360
of farmers who implement 1

00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:20.720
food social security,

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:22.600
of an artist who saves animals

00:00:22.680 --> 00:00:24.400
and many other stories of people

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:25.840
ordinary that have 1 day

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:27.640
decided that they could change the world.

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:29.600
This is a book that gives

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:31.400
ideas to live differently

00:00:31.480 --> 00:00:32.880
and to engage in struggles.

00:00:32.920 --> 00:00:35.200
To be found now in your bookstores!
